cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with learning aesthetically-relevant visual attributes from images. The use of a convolutional neural network (CNN) also supports this assumption. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.MM) as it uses a weakly-supervised learning algorithm to project textual attributes at image-level to pixel-level. Additionally, the use of a sparsity-constrained subspace algorithm suggests that this paper may also belong to the machine learning sub-category. The paper may also belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves image retargeting, aesthetics ranking, and retrieval, which are related to these sub-categories.
